post_text:
Due to air quality we will not be serving meals tomorrow, Monday, August 24th. We will resume service on Tuesday, August 25th and Thursday, August 27th. Meals can be picked up from 9 AM to 1 PM at Bolsa Knolls Middle School, New Republic Elementary, and Santa Rita Elementary. You will receive meals for 2 days. There will be no meal service on Wednesday and Friday this week.

Debido a la calidad del aire, no serviremos comidas mañana, lunes 24 de agosto. Reanudaremos el servicio el martes 25 de agosto y el jueves 27 de agosto. Las comidas se pueden recoger de 9 am a 1 pm en Bolsa Knolls Middle School, New Republic Elementary y Santa Rita Elementary. Recibirás comidas durante 2 días. No habrá servicio de comidas los miércoles y viernes de esta semana.

We are excited to announce that we will be using Edlio Engage, a family engagement platform to help families stay connected and engaged in their child’s learning experiences! The platform will be implemented across all of our schools for the 2020-21 school year & beyond. Look for a welcome email and/or text message within the next two weeks. More information can be found on our district website santaritaschools.org.

¡Nos complace anunciar que utilizaremos Edlio Engage, una plataforma de participación familiar para ayudar a las familias a mantenerse conectadas y comprometidas con las experiencias de aprendizaje de sus hijos! La plataforma se implementará en todas nuestras escuelas para el año escolar 2020-21 y más allá. Busque un correo electrónico y / o mensaje de texto de bienvenida dentro de las próximas dos semanas. Puede encontrar más información en el sitio web de nuestro distrito santaritaschools.org.

shared_text:
Monterey County Office of Education
December 18, 2019 at 4:21 PM ·

Exciting news from the California Department of Education!

Two Monterey County elementary schools are being honored as 2020 California Distinguished Schools by the California Department of Education. Schools are awarded for their work toward closing the achievement gap and for achieving exceptional student performance. Schools that applied were eligible based on their performance and progress on the state indicators as described on the California School Dashboard. Indicators include test scores, suspension rates and English learner progress.

The two schools are:
* Monte Vista Elementary School in the Monterey Peninsula Unified School District
* New Republic Elementary School in the Santa Rita Union Elementary School District

The 323 California Distinguished Schools will be honored on February 10, 2020, during an awards ceremony at the Disneyland Resort in Anaheim. The complete list of honorees is available - https://www.cde.ca.gov/nr/ne/yr19/yr19rel85.asp.
